==English==

===Etymology===
Derived from [[blog]] or web log, an online journal generally updated very often.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒɡə(r)|-ɒɡə(r)]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{internet}} a [[contributor]] to a [[blog]] or [[online]] [[journal]]. A blogger can write about any [[topic]]. Though often in the press bloggers are meant to refer to journalists amateur or professional who run a blog.
# {{internet}} a website, [http://www.blogger.com http://www.blogger.com], offering free hosting and tools to create a [[blog]]. See [[wikipedia:Blogger.com|Wikipedia's entry for 'Blogger.com']].
# {{internet}} someone using the internet as a medium to express and report about what has moved him. Using words, pictures, photos and videos, the blogger often reahmicks content from different sources like traditionnal media, community sites, other blogs and content providers. Blogs range from any topic: personnal diaries, technology blogs, cooking blogs, traveling blogs, music blogs, ...

===Derived terms===
*[[blogette]] - female blogger

